data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your manual expression-tree construction **won't compile** because the overload now accepts a plain lambda. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Much simpler ŌĆö dynamic conditionals now work inline.

---

### 2. Complex type columns ŌĆö names are now uniquified & nested paths changed

Two sub-changes:

- **Duplicate names get a numeric suffix.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` no longer silently share one column ŌĆö the second gets `Street1`.
- **Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of `BillingAddress_City`.

Both generate new migrations that rename columns. To **preserve existing column names** and avoid data migration, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street")); // keep shared column
});

// For nested complex types, pin to the old shorter name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual execution SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
